# CODEOWNERS
#
# Maps repository paths to subsystem owners for GitHub's review-assignment
# feature, and doubles as documentation of who owns what (see
# docs/requirements/01-team-and-collaboration.md: each student owns one
# primary subsystem — client, server, or GenAI — but collaborates across
# boundaries for integration, deployment, and debugging).
#
# The names below are role placeholders, NOT usable GitHub handles. GitHub
# silently ignores entries that aren't real usernames/teams with repo access,
# so this file has no effect until each placeholder is replaced with the
# actual GitHub username of that subsystem's owner:
#
#   @client-owner  -> web-client owner's GitHub username
#   @server-owner  -> Spring services owner's GitHub username
#   @genai-owner   -> GenAI service owner's GitHub username
#
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default: shared review across all three owners for anything not matched below
* @client-owner @server-owner @genai-owner

# Client
/web-client/ @client-owner

# Server (Spring Boot microservices)
/services/spring/ @server-owner

# GenAI service
/services/gen-ai/ @genai-owner

# Cross-cutting / shared responsibility: infra, CI/CD, API contract, docs
/infra/ @client-owner @server-owner @genai-owner
/.github/ @client-owner @server-owner @genai-owner
/api/ @client-owner @server-owner @genai-owner
/docs/ @client-owner @server-owner @genai-owner
